Inspired by the Touying Typst slides package
(https://github.com/touying-typ/touying, MIT License). This minimal
subset implements a small, Touying-compatible API: `slide`, `title-slide`,
`section-slide`, `focus-slide`. It is NOT a fork of Touying — no source
files are copied — but it follows Touying's API surface so a project can
later migrate to upstream Touying without rewriting slide content.

